b'{"warnings":{"query":{"*":"Formatting of continuation data will be changing soon. To continue using the current formatting, use the \'rawcontinue\' parameter. To begin using the new format, pass an empty string for \'continue\' in the initial query."}},"query":{"pages":{"15304272":{"pageid":15304272,"ns":0,"title":"Mother Night (comics)","revisions":[{"contentformat":"text/x-wiki","contentmodel":"wikitext","*":"{{Superherobox| <!--Wikipedia:WikiProject Comics--> \\nimage=\\n|caption=\\n|comic_color=background:#ff8080 \\n|character_name=Mother Night\\n|real_name=Susan Scarbo\\n|species=\\n|publisher=[[Marvel Comics]]\\n|debut=\'\'[[Captain America]] #123\'\' (Mar 1970)\\n|creators=[[Stan Lee]] and [[Gene Colan]]\\n|alliance_color=background:#c0c0ff\\n|alliances=[[Skeleton Crew (comics)|Skeleton Crew]]<br/>[[Sisters of Sin]]\\n|aliases=Suprema\\n|powers=Illusions, hypnosis, martial arts, can project \'\'dark light\'\' to vanish into shadows, and possesses a necklace that emits a mind-subverting gas\\n|}} \\n\\n\'\'\'Mother Night\'\'\' is a fictional character in the [[Marvel Universe]].\\n\\n==Fictional character biography==\\nSusan Scarbo was born in [[Teaneck, New Jersey]]. Susan and her brother Melvin Scarbo formed a sibling hypnosis stage act for profit. They soon after became professional criminals, hypnotizing innocent people into doing their bidding. Under the name Suprema, Susan soon attracted the attention of the [[Red Skull]] who hired Susan as a nanny to his daughter Synthia Schmidt. Under Susan\'s tutelage Synthia later became [[Sin (Marvel Comics)|Sin]].\\n\\nAfter a successful infiltration of the original [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] organization and an attempt at stealing a Wolverine Jet from them, Suprema became an enemy of [[Captain America]].<ref>\'\'Captain America\'\' #123</ref> Some time later, Susan was revealed as an aide to the Red Skull, and his daughter Sin\'s tutor, nanny, and instructor.<ref>\'\'Captain America\'\' #350</ref> Changing her name to Mother Night, she became the headmistress of the [[Sisters of Sin]] team for a short while, and was revealed to be running the Red Skull\'s youth indoctrination hate camp.<ref>\'\'Captain America\'\' #356</ref> When [[Magneto (comics)|Magneto]] captured the Red Skull, Mother Night became a member of the [[Skeleton Crew (comics)|Skeleton Crew]] in an attempt to rescue the Red Skull. She battled the [[Selene (comics)|Black Queen]] and her [[Hellfire Club (comics)|Hellfire Club]] mercenaries.<ref>\'\'Captain America\'\' #369</ref> She aided the Crew in the rescue of the Red Skull, and it was insinuated that she has or had a personal relationship with the Red Skull.<ref>\'\'Captain America\'\' #370</ref>\\n\\nMother Night, with the [[Machinesmith]] and Minster Blood (her brother Melvin) then brainwashed the Avengers\' support crew. She attacked the [[Avengers (comics)|Avengers]] by forcing them to relive their greatest nightmares, however she was captured by the [[Vision (Marvel Comics)|Vision]].<ref>\'\'Avengers\'\' #324-325</ref> After this Red Skull replaced Mother Night with [[Viper (Marvel Comics)|Viper]] as his lover.{{Issue|date=April 2010}} Because of this she betrayed him to Captain America and received a severe beating from Red Skull for it.{{Issue|date=April 2010}} Wishing to die at her ex-lover\'s hand she asked Red Skull to kill her, to which he said no.{{Issue|date=April 2010}} Pitying her, teammate [[Cutthroat (comics)|Cutthroat]] began an affair with Mother Night.{{Issue|date=April 2010}} This relationship ended when he was seemingly killed by [[Crossbones (comics)|Crossbones]].{{Issue|date=April 2010}}\\n\\nShe and her team were eventually killed by [[Bucky|The Winter Soldier]].{{Issue|date=June 2009}}\\n\\n==Other versions==\\n===Marvel Max===\\nIn Wolverine Max, she moved in a trailer park in Las Vegas, Nevada. She meets Wolverine after watching him in an unsanctioned MMA fight. They have sex, and during pillow talk, she mentions that she is from Tea Neck, New Jersey.  It is later revealed that she is not a psychic, but a hypnotist. She obtained her black sapphire from Brazil, and works as an independent hypnotist by \\"appointment only\\". As she is talking, Wolverine suddenly becomes ill, and passes out. Wolverine beginning confused, ends up getting into a fight, only to find out his claws won\'t pop out. He storms back to her trailer, to find out what she did to him.<ref>\'\'Wolverine: MAX\'\' #11</ref> He is in Mother Night\'s control. She orders him to hate and kill a man named Max Fisher with rage and anguish. After is last fight in the ring, he takes Sean\'s van and heads to confront Max Fisher<ref>\'\'Wolverine MAX\'\' #12</ref> It turns out Mother Night was married to Max Fisher, and used Wolverine to kill him to get a hold of his fortune. It\'s also revealed that Sean and Mother Night were working together. Wolverine managed to get his memory back by shooting his head with a double barrel shotgun. He then meets up with Mother Night, while he is pretending to be hypnotized. He confronts her and slices her jugular, effectively killing her.<ref>\'\'Wolverine MAX\'\' #13</ref>\\n\\n==Powers and abilities==\\nMother Night has developed a mastery of hypnotism. Mother Night has to get a person to look at her for her hypnotic abilities to work. Certain individuals are not susceptible to hypnotism.\\n\\nMother Night has a limited knowledge of street-fighting techniques and karate.\\n\\nMother Night\'s necklace contains a special suggestibility gas as well as a \\"dark light\\" casting mechanism. She also uses various brainwashing drugs and paraphernalia.\\n\\n==References==\\n{{Reflist}}\\n\\n==External links==\\n* [http://www.marvel.com/universe/Mother_Night Mother Night] at Marvel.com\\n* {{Marvunapp|http://www.marvunapp.com/Appendix2/mothernight.htm|Mother Night}}\\n\\n[[Category:Characters created by Gene Colan]]\\n[[Category:Characters created by Stan Lee]]\\n[[Category:Comics characters introduced in 1970]]\